TextEquiv.Unicode: 1 When shall the voice of singing
And Him who once was slain ,
1 When shall the voice of singing Flow joyfully along ? When hill and valley , ringing With one triumphant song , Proclaim the contest ended , And Him who once was slain , Again to earth descended ,
2 Then from the craggy mountains , The sacred shout shall fly ; And shady vales and fountains Shall echo the reply .
High tower and lowly dwelling Shall send the chorus round , All hallelujahs swelling , In one eternal sound !
Gently lead us by the hand ,
While they hear that sweetest voice ,
Follow me , I'll guide thee home .

1 Holy Spirit , faithful Guide , Ever near the Christian's side , Gently lead us by the hand , Pilgrims in a desert land . Weary souls , fore'er rejoice , While they hear that sweetest voice , Whisp'ring softly , wanderer , come ! Follow me , I'll guide thee home .
Go when the moon is bright ,
Go in the hush of night ;
Go with pure mind and feeling ,

1 Go when the morning shineth , Go when the moon is bright , Go when the eve declineth , Go in the hush of night ; Go with pure mind and feeling , Drive earthly thoughts away , And , in thy closet kneeling , Do thou in secret pray .
And who are loved by thee ;
Pray , too , for those who hate thee ,
Then , for thyself , in meekness , A blessing humbly claim And blend with each petition Thy great Redeemer's name .
Ever near , thine aid to lend ,
Leave us not to doubt and fear ,
When the storms are raging sore ,
Hearts grow faint and hopes give o'er ,
Follow me , I'll guide thee home .

2 Ever present , truest friend , Ever near , thine aid to lend , Leave us not to doubt and fear , Groping on in darkness drear . When the storms are raging sore , Hearts grow faint and hopes give o'er , Whisper softly , wanderer , come ! Follow me , I'll guide thee home .
1 I want to be like Jesus ,
For no one marked an angry word
I want to be like Jesus ,
1 I want to be like Jesus , So lowly and so meek ; For no one marked an angry word That ever heard him speak . I want to be like Jesus ,
2 I want to be like Jesus ;
2 I want to be like Jesus ; I never , never find
That he , though persecuted , was To any one unkind .
I want to be like Jesus ,
I want to be like Jesus ,
So that of me it may be said ,
So that of me it may be said ,
" She hath done what she could . "
" She hath done what she could . "
3 When our days of toil shall cease ,
Nothing left but heaven and prayer ,
Wond'ring if our names are there ;
Follow me , I'll guide thee home .

3 When our days of toil shall cease , Waiting still for sweet release , Nothing left but heaven and prayer , Wond'ring if our names are there ; Wading deep the dismal flood , Pleading naught but Jesus ' blood ; Whisper softly , wanderer come ! Follow me , I'll guide thee home .
